nano gives a text editor where we can create different types of files such as .txt, .py, .cpp etc
######Some shortcuts:
Ctrl+Shift+dash=Go to a line
Alt+U = Undo
Alt+E = Redo
Alt+6 = Copy


fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~$ cd Desktop/
fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ ls
Bangladesh.txt  folder2

fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ nano file.txt   ;Creating a new file
fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ ls
Bangladesh.txt  file.txt  folder2

fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ nano file.txt   ;This file is already created. I edited it here
fokhrul@fokhrul-VirtualBox:~/Desktop$ nano abc.py     ;creating a .py file(python)

